<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Desiac</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-26 23:24:43</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white> I spent 10k pp to get my skill to 195. Thinking I should be ready to make some plat with just a little more of a failure rate than if I were at 200 I promised to make this item for someone. 3kpp later I made it. So it took me 3kpp to make something for someone. As far as failures being so high now I can't compare it with before. I have petitioned the GM's 3 times with only rude comments and no answers back from them about this. Then you go out to sell jewelry and you get rude comments from people on prices. On Tarew Mar I sell a Silver Ruby Vail for 175pp. Do you know how many people ask me if I will sell it for 100pp and less? People need to get educated on the expenses in jewel craft. And they need to stop being so rude to jewelers for without them they would have nothing to buy they would have to go out and kill everything 20 times to get a good drop. Please people do not ask a jeweler to make something for you at cost or if you supply the materials. Even trivial stuff fails. Prices are adjusted to make it fair to the jeweler and the buyers so that no one is getting cheated. If you don't like the price... tell them you want to do some shopping around. Don't critisize them especially when you are ignorant of the costs involved. Please go to some of the sites available to you and educate yourselves on the items you wish to buy and the prices they should be going for. It will make your search and a jewelers so much easier if you know exactly what you want and you know what kind of price to expect. Thanks all and be safe and happy jewelry hunting :-)</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Niam D'Sparil</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-07 15:43:34</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Just to start:  Jewelcrafting (like all other trades) caps<BR>
at 200 skill.  As a crafter with a skill of 185, I can tell<BR>
you that yes, no platinum jewelry every trivializes, and the<BR>
higher the stone (sapphire, rubies, etc), the more likely <BR>
you will fail.  I fail about 2/3 times on the plat ruby veil.<BR>
Yeah, it sucks, which is probably why I only do jewelcrafting<BR>
for my guild now :)  I find it unforunate that besides this<BR>
trade there really isn't much demand for the other trades.<BR>
Just my opinion.<BR>
<BR>
Niam<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
