<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Izarneth</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-22 18:49:24</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Kaelith listed the ruby at 150 and the plat at 110(I think)<BR>
Thats probly what they cost him.  But remember enchanters get +10 to cha from class choice, many throw a few more points into it, and most pick a race with a good cha(ie high elf).  Enchanters also usually have some +cha equip. The reason is that in a ddition to it helping reduce their jewelling cost, cha also affects charming and mezzing(some debate here, but leave that for another day, either way most chanters have high char).  Also, to make plat jewelry you have to be 34, which means you have char buffing spells.  What this all means is that enchanters can get the materials for a lot less than most of us ugly warriors(J/K).  So the price of the stuff for them is more like 125 and 95, respectively.  Oh, I forgot to mention they can boost their faction with spells and change to the race of the vendor to ensure a good price.  This doesnt mean they shouldnt charge a lot for stuff....like has been said jewelling plat stuff never becomes triv, and these high end gems are even harder to work with, but the cost of the materials isnt quite as high as you would think, based on what it would cost you to buy the stuff.  This is also why you probly shouldnt provide the materials, let chanters buy it cheaper and use the diff as part of their profit, why give plat to a merchant when you could give it to a player?</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
